ON FRIDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND SW INTO THE NITON
AREA LINKING UP WITH THE AZORES HIGH TO THE W. THROUGH SATURDAY A FURTHER
LARGE HIGH WILL BUILD TO BE CENTRED NEAR THE NW OF THE FCST AREA BY MIDNIGHT
SUNDAY AS PRESSURE FALLS ACROSS IBERIA. THE RIDGE IN THE E WILL ALSO PERSIST
THROUGH SATURDAY. SUNDAY IS LIKELY TO SEE THE HIGH BECOME SLOW MOV TO THE
SW OF THE BRITISH ISLES AS PRESSURE FALLS IN THE EERN ENGLISH CHANNEL AND
SERN N SEA. HIGH PRESSURE LIKELY TO BE MAINTAINED OVER MUCH OF THE AREA THROUGH
MONDAY BUT WITH A CYCLONIC FLOW DEVELOPING AGAIN IN THE SERN N SEA BY EVENING.
WINDS LIKELY TO BECOME STRG AT TIMES IN S FITZROY FM LATE SATURDAY. STRG
